---
/**
 * The Soft Footsteps Society — a future doorway.
 * A poetic seed, deliberately not overbuilt.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageTitle from '../components/sections/PageTitle.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/sections/CTASection.astro';
import { routes } from '../lib/i18n';

const futureThings = [
  'Letters from the road',
  'Postcards, occasionally urgent',
  'Small drawings',
  'Field assignments — gentle homework for the attentive',
  'Seasonal dispatches',
  'Enrollment, for those who wish to walk softly on purpose',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Soft Footsteps Society"
  description="A society for people who want to move through the world with more attention, tenderness, curiosity, and less destruction. Currently being founded. Enrollment not yet open."
  lang="en"
  translationUrl={routes.softFootsteps.pt}
>
  <PageTitle
    overline="A future doorway"
    title="The Soft Footsteps Society"
    lede="In Portuguese: Sociedade dos Passos Suaves. A society for people who want to move through the world with more attention, tenderness, curiosity — and less destruction."
  />

  <section class="section society-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The Society does not fully exist yet. This is not a problem. Most good institutions spend
          some time as rumors first.
        </p>
        <p>
          What is known so far: it will be a correspondence society — part snail-mail club, part
          art project, part very informal school of attention. Members will receive things in the
          mail. They will occasionally be given small assignments, such as
          <em>"find a tree older than your country and apologize to it for nothing in particular."</em>
          There will be no leaderboard. There will be no streaks. Progress will be measured in
          noticing.
        </p>

        <h2>What the Society will send</h2>
        <ul>
          {futureThings.map((thing) => <li>{thing}</li>)}
        </ul>

        <h2>The staff, allegedly</h2>
        <p>
          The Society is said to be founded by <strong>Professor Elai Emberroot</strong>, field
          professor of attention, whose office is a motorhome and whose office hours depend on the
          weather. There is also talk of an <strong>Archivist</strong>, keeper of the notes, whose
          identity remains — appropriately — filed away. Departments have been proposed: a library,
          a map room, a correspondence desk, a creature archive. None have been built. All have
          been imagined, which is how buildings start.
        </p>

        <h2>Enrollment</h2>
        <p>
          Not yet open. The desk is being built, and the desk insists on being built well. If you
          would like to be told when the Society opens its doors, you can
          <a href={routes.contact.en}>write to the camp</a> and say so — early letters will be
          answered in order of arrival, weather permitting.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the meantime, the only requirement for future membership is already available to you:
          go outside, walk slower than necessary, and notice one thing that has no use to you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    overline="Meanwhile"
    title="The letters have already begun."
    text="The Society's first correspondence is drafted at the camp desk. You can read it now."
    cta={{ label: 'Read Correspondence No. 001', href: `${routes.correspondence.en}no-001/` }}
    secondaryCta={{ label: 'Write to the camp', href: routes.contact.en }}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .society-body {
    padding-block: var(--space-block) var(--space-section);
  }
</style>
